<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 3:46PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...ICY CONDITIONS POSSIBLE WEDNESDAY MORNING...
Light precipitation, associated with a weak low pressure system,
is expected to develop over the area after 4 AM Wednesday.
Conditions may be cold enough to allow for a period of freezing
rain, especially at or near the onset. This freezing rain will be
capable of producing hazardous conditions on area roadways. Any
freezing rain is expected to change over to plain rain by 10 AM.</description>
